# 1) Unzip into your workspace
unzip GODMODE-000-111-EXT2-ledger-banks.zip
cd GODMODE-000-111-EXT2

# 2) Set up a virtual environment and install
python -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt

# 3) Configure environment
cp .env.example .env
# Set:
# - INVITE_CODES (e.g., alpha-000)
# - PRIVATE_KEY (testnet only!)
# - ETH_RPC (e.g., Sepolia/Rinkeby)
# - ALLOWLIST = your controller address
# Optionally, assign ADMINS or OPERATORS roles in .env

# 4) Launch the app
uvicorn app:app --reload

# 5) Open in your browser
http://127.0.0.1:8000

Enter your invite code, and youâ€™ll access the UI with:
- Dashboard (000/111 aesthetic)
- Sequence runner (dry run)
- Bank Ops forms (Simplii / KOHO stubs)
- Transaction ledger logged under `tx_ledger/`

connect()         # get a client
get_balance()     # per token
transfer(...)     # send funds
yield_ops(...)    # deposit/stake/


















